1
00:00:04,316 --> 00:00:09,887
That which is auspicious, you should
do immediately without hesitation,

2
00:00:09,887 --> 00:00:18,464
and that which is inauspicious, 
you should delay, delay, wait, wait and see.

3
00:00:18,464 --> 00:00:21,818
He who acts hurriedly
will have to repent, this kind of thing.

4
00:00:22,495 --> 00:00:25,752
[Rāvaṇ’s Good Advice]

5
00:00:26,169 --> 00:00:30,609
When he told us this advice,
we were surprised—

6
00:00:30,609 --> 00:00:34,201
who’s the source of this?

7
00:00:34,201 --> 00:00:38,966
It’s great wisdom, everyone
will benefit from hearing it:

8
00:00:38,966 --> 00:00:43,335
that which is auspicious,
do immediately without hesitation;

9
00:00:43,335 --> 00:00:48,666
that which is inauspicious, delay it,
put it off, don’t rush into that.

10
00:00:48,666 --> 00:00:52,564
‘Fools rush in where angels
fear to tread’—this whole idea.

11
00:00:52,589 --> 00:00:58,413
So Guru Mahārāj said, 
“Where does this come from? It’s from Rāvaṇa,

12
00:00:58,413 --> 00:01:02,386
the demon, 
the ten-headed demon, Rāvaṇa.”

13
00:01:02,386 --> 00:01:05,933
How does it happen?
After all these pastimes take place,

14
00:01:05,933 --> 00:01:10,929
and he’s lying and dying
on the battlefield.

15
00:01:12,189 --> 00:01:15,745
Guru Mahārāj said,
Rāmachandra told Lakṣmaṇ,

16
00:01:15,745 --> 00:01:22,003
“You go and get some advice from him;
he has some valuable knowledge

17
00:01:22,003 --> 00:01:27,203
about the world, about life,
about experience. Go and approach him.”

18
00:01:27,203 --> 00:01:30,428
And he said at first Lakṣmaṇ goes
to where his head is

19
00:01:30,428 --> 00:01:32,966
because he’s lying on the battlefield
dying, and Rāma says,

20
00:01:32,966 --> 00:01:36,138
“No, no, no.
If you’re to take instruction,

21
00:01:36,138 --> 00:01:38,571
then you should sit at the feet.”

22
00:01:38,571 --> 00:01:43,638
That’s the proper way to approach;
sit at the lotus feet of the instructor.

23
00:01:43,638 --> 00:01:48,229
So, he’s sitting at the feet of Rāvaṇa
and inquiring from him,

24
00:01:48,245 --> 00:01:50,114
“What have you learned in life?

25
00:01:50,114 --> 00:01:52,631
What valuable wisdom
can you impart to me?”

26
00:01:52,631 --> 00:01:54,670
And that’s when Rāvaṇa says,

27
00:01:54,670 --> 00:01:58,062
śubhasya śīghram aśubhasya kāla-haraṇam

28
00:01:58,062 --> 00:02:02,194
“Everyone told me,
‘Don’t go against Rāmachandra’.

29
00:02:02,194 --> 00:02:06,184
Everyone told me,
‘Do not kidnap his wife, Sītā Devī’.

30
00:02:06,184 --> 00:02:09,389
Everyone told me,
‘This is a bad idea.’

31
00:02:09,389 --> 00:02:13,038
Every last person.
I ran it by different people,

32
00:02:13,038 --> 00:02:15,303
nobody signed on to this.

33
00:02:15,303 --> 00:02:18,955
They all said, ‘Bad idea, don’t do it,
please don’t do this,

34
00:02:18,955 --> 00:02:22,595
it’s going to be the end of you,
it’s going to be your ruination.’”

35
00:02:22,595 --> 00:02:26,270
He said,
“But I didn’t listen to them.

36
00:02:26,270 --> 00:02:31,819
I had these other good programs.”
Like, he had The Stairway to Heaven,

37
00:02:31,835 --> 00:02:36,949
The Mango Program—
mangoes come from Sri Lanka …

38
00:02:37,549 --> 00:02:39,910
Different kinds … The city was very nice.

39
00:02:39,910 --> 00:02:43,504
He said, “But those I stopped,
I stopped developing them.

40
00:02:43,504 --> 00:02:48,853
But this bad program,
fight with Rāmachandra, steal his wife,

41
00:02:48,853 --> 00:02:54,032
I just rushed into it, full blown,
with passion, didn’t listen to anybody,

42
00:02:54,032 --> 00:02:58,367
against all good advice.”
And he said, “Look at me now.”

43
00:02:58,383 --> 00:03:01,482
So, that which is auspicious,
do it immediately;

44
00:03:01,482 --> 00:03:06,095
that which is inauspicious,
delay, delay, wait, don’t do that.

